{"title_page": "Destiny (streamer)", "text_new": "\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=May 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox Twitch streamer\n| name = Destiny \n| logo =\n| logo_caption =\n| image = ModernDayDebateDestiny2020.png\n| caption = Bonnell debating at a public event in 2020\n| birth_name = Steven Bonnell II\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = [[Omaha, Nebraska]], U.S.\n| residence = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| nationality = American\n| occupation = Twitch streamer/YouTuber\n| website = [http://destiny.gg destiny.gg]\n| channel_name = Destiny\n| years_active = 2011\u2013present\n| genre = [[Video gaming]], [[political commentary]]\n| games = {{flatlist|\n* ''[[League of Legends]]''\n* ''[[PlayerUnknown's Battlegrounds]]''\n* ''[[Minecraft]]''\n* ''[[Call of Duty: Black Ops 4]]''\n* ''[[StarCraft II (disambiguation)|Starcraft II]]''<!--intentional link to DAB page-->\n}}\n| followers =536,505 \n| views =99,564,618 \n| follower_date = \n| view_date = \n| stats_update =April 16, 2020 \n}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name                 = \n| channel_display_name = Destiny\n| genre                = Politics/Gaming\n| subscribers          = 224 thousand\n| subscriber_date      = April 16, 2020\n| views                = 109 million\n| view_date            = April 16, 2020\n| silver_button        = Yes\n| silver_year          = March 2018\n}}\n'''Steven Kenneth Bonnell II''', better known by his online [[Pseudonym|alias]] '''Destiny''', is an American [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] [[Live streaming|streamer]] and [[List of YouTube personalities|YouTube personality]]. Bonnell was among the first people to commit to full-time streaming and received some attention as a pioneer of the emerging industry.<ref name=\"vergeWhy\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2014/8/26/6068993/this-is-why-people-want-to-watch-other-people-play-video-games|title=This is why people want to watch other people play video games|last1=McCormick|first1=Rich|website=The Verge|accessdate=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nBonnell grew up in Omaha in a conservative Catholic home.<ref name=\":1\" /> When he was in his teens his parents moved to take care of an aging relative and he lived with his grandmother until he was 18.<ref name=\":1\" /> He attended the University of Nebraska, working at a local casino and dropping out in 2010.<ref name=\":1\" /> He worked in restaurants and as a carpet cleaner.<ref>{{Citation|last=Destiny|title=My Life Before I Started Streaming|date=2016-05-17|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mZ7xypQy_Ks|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://blog.destiny.gg/my-journey-in-streaming/|title=My Journey In Streaming|last=Destiny|website=Destiny|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Career ==\n\n\nBonnell began his online career as a professional ''[[StarCraft II: Wings of Liberty|Starcraft 2]]'' player who livestreamed his matches.<ref name=\"vergeWhy\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edge-online.com/features/inside-the-new-world-of-247-on-demand-videogame-tv/|title=Inside the new world of 24/7 on-demand videogame TV|last=|first=|date=July 1, 2013|website=[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130707111129/http://www.edge-online.com/features/inside-the-new-world-of-247-on-demand-videogame-tv/|archivedate=July 7, 2013|accessdate=June 24, 2019}}</ref> According to Bonnell, he first started livestreaming in January 2011 on the website [[Justin.tv]].<ref name=\":0\" /> Bonnell eventually signed with Quantic Gaming.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/157679/Steven_ldquoDestinyrdquo_Bonnell_joins_Quantic%0AGaming.php|title=Steven \u201cDestiny\u201d Bonnell joins Quantic Gaming|website=www.gamasutra.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> Later, Bonnell would end up 4th in the 2011 MLG Global North American invitational.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://liquipedia.net/starcraft2/2011_MLG_Global_Invitational | title=2011 MLG Global Invitational - Liquipedia - the StarCraft II Encyclopedia}}</ref>{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\nBonnell has also received coverage for his live-streamed political debates.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.wired.com/story/twitch-politics-online-debate/|title=Can This Notorious Troll Turn People Away From Extremism?|work=Wired|access-date=2020-04-16|language=en|issn=1059-1028}}</ref> Bonnell, along with [[Natalie Wynn]], were credited by Caleb Cain for his turn away from the [[alt-right]].<ref name=\":1\" /> Bonnell describes himself as a [[rule utilitarianism|rule ultilitarian]]<ref name=\"Politics, philosophy, religion and more - Destiny AMA\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qvlkFu_KFmA&feature=youtu.be&t=676|title= Destiny. Politics, philosophy, religion and more - Destiny AMA|accessdate=19 April 2020|date=2020-04-16}}</ref> and a [[social democrat]].<ref name=\"Politics, philosophy, religion and more\">{{cite web|url=\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qvlkFu_KFmA&feature=youtu.be&t=43|title=Destiny. Politics, philosophy, religion and more - Destiny AMA|accessdate=19 April 2020|date=2020-04-16}}</ref> \n\nThroughout Bonnell's early career, he was well known for his provocative persona and common use of crass language.<ref name=\"vergeWhy\"/> This led to temporary suspensions from the Twitch platform for insensitive language. In February 2018, Bonnell was temporarily banned from Twitch for the use of the words \"faggot\" and \"retard\" as part of a joke.<ref name=\"polygon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/7/3/17530920/twitch-ban-destiny-m0e-alfie-hateful-conduct-youtube|title=Destiny, M0E, Alfie and other Twitch streamers banned as company crack down|website=Polygon|accessdate=30 October 2018|date=2018-07-03}}</ref> \n\nA debate between Bonnell and well-known YouTuber [[JonTron]] became popular.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/4701304/jontron-jon-jafari-steve-bonnell-immigration-race-youtube/|title=YouTube Star JonTron Under Fire for Comments on Race and Immigration|website=Time|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\nBonnell is known for going 2/7 in the popular [[MOBA]] [[League of Legends]].\n== Personal life ==\nBonnell lives in Los Angeles.<ref name=\":1\" /> He has a son who lives in Nebraska.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Twitch streamers]]\n[[Category:American agnostics]]\n[[Category:People from Omaha, Nebraska]]\n[[Category:American people of Cuban descent]]\n[[Category:University of Nebraska alumni]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use American English|date=May 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox Twitch streamer\n| name = Destiny \n| logo =\n| logo_caption =\n| image = ModernDayDebateDestiny2020.png\n| caption = Bonnell debating at a public event in 2020\n| birth_name = Steven Bonnell II\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = [[Omaha, Nebraska]], U.S.\n| residence = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| nationality = American\n| occupation = Twitch streamer/YouTuber\n| website = [http://destiny.gg destiny.gg]\n| channel_name = Destiny\n| years_active = 2011\u2013present\n| genre = [[Video gaming]], [[political commentary]]\n| games = {{flatlist|\n* ''[[League of Legends]]''\n* ''[[PlayerUnknown's Battlegrounds]]''\n* ''[[Minecraft]]''\n* ''[[Call of Duty: Black Ops 4]]''\n* ''[[StarCraft II (disambiguation)|Starcraft II]]''<!--intentional link to DAB page-->\n}}\n| followers =536,505 \n| views =99,564,618 \n| follower_date = \n| view_date = \n| stats_update =April 16, 2020 \n}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name                 = \n| channel_display_name = Destiny\n| genre                = Politics/Gaming\n| subscribers          = 224 thousand\n| subscriber_date      = April 16, 2020\n| views                = 109 million\n| view_date            = April 16, 2020\n| silver_button        = Yes\n| silver_year          = March 2018\n}}\n'''Steven Kenneth Bonnell II''', better known by his online [[Pseudonym|alias]] '''Destiny''', is an American [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]] [[Live streaming|streamer]] and [[List of YouTube personalities|YouTube personality]]. Bonnell was among the first people to commit to full-time streaming and received some attention as a pioneer of the emerging industry.<ref name=\"vergeWhy\">{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2014/8/26/6068993/this-is-why-people-want-to-watch-other-people-play-video-games|title=This is why people want to watch other people play video games|last1=McCormick|first1=Rich|website=The Verge|accessdate=13 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nBonnell grew up in Omaha in a conservative Catholic home.<ref name=\":1\" /> When he was in his teens his parents moved to take care of an aging relative and he lived with his grandmother until he was 18.<ref name=\":1\" /> He attended the University of Nebraska, working at a local casino and dropping out in 2010.<ref name=\":1\" /> He worked in restaurants and as a carpet cleaner.<ref>{{Citation|last=Destiny|title=My Life Before I Started Streaming|date=2016-05-17|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mZ7xypQy_Ks|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://blog.destiny.gg/my-journey-in-streaming/|title=My Journey In Streaming|last=Destiny|website=Destiny|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== Career ==\n\n\nBonnell began his online career as a professional ''[[StarCraft II: Wings of Liberty|Starcraft 2]]'' player who livestreamed his matches.<ref name=\"vergeWhy\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edge-online.com/features/inside-the-new-world-of-247-on-demand-videogame-tv/|title=Inside the new world of 24/7 on-demand videogame TV|last=|first=|date=July 1, 2013|website=[[Edge (magazine)|Edge]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130707111129/http://www.edge-online.com/features/inside-the-new-world-of-24