his led to temporary suspensions from the Twitch platform for insensitive language. In February 2018, Bonnell was temporarily banned from Twitch for the use of the words \"faggot\" and \"retard\" as part of a joke.<ref name=\"polygon\">{{cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/2018/7/3/17530920/twitch-ban-destiny-m0e-alfie-hateful-conduct-youtube|title=Destiny, M0E, Alfie and other Twitch streamers banned as company crack down|website=Polygon|accessdate=30 October 2018|date=2018-07-03}}</ref> \n\nA debate between Bonnell and well-known YouTuber [[JonTron]] became popular.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/4701304/jontron-jon-jafari-steve-bonnell-immigration-race-youtube/|title=YouTube Star JonTron Under Fire for Comments on Race and Immigration|website=Time|language=en|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nBonnell lives in Los Angeles.<ref name=\":1\" /> He has a son who lives in Nebraska.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Twitch streamers]]\n[[Category:American agnostics]]\n[[Category:People from Omaha, Nebraska]]\n[[Category:American people of Cuban descent]]\n[[Category:University of Nebraska alumni]]\n", "name_user": "81.21.245.178", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destiny_(streamer)"}
